<?xml version='1.0' encoding='ISO-8859-1' ?>
<grammar>
<section>
<title>Present simple: positive and negative forms: &lt;i&gt;I&lt;/i&gt;,&lt;i&gt; you&lt;/i&gt;,&lt;i&gt; we&lt;/i&gt;,&lt;i&gt; they&lt;/i&gt;</title>
<sectiontitle>&lt;/b&gt;In the positive, we use &lt;i&gt;I/you/we/they&lt;/i&gt; + verb.</sectiontitle>
<titlesound>el_gram_3_2_1.mp3</titlesound>
<text1></text1>
<text1a>&lt;b&gt;We work&lt;/b&gt; for a big company.</text1a>
<sound1>el_gram_3_2_2.mp3</sound1>
<text2> </text2>
<text2a>&lt;b&gt;You speak&lt;/b&gt; Chinese well.</text2a>
<sound2>el_gram_3_2_3.mp3</sound2>
<sectiontitle2>&lt;/b&gt;In the negative, we use &lt;i&gt;I/you/we/they&lt;/i&gt; + &lt;i&gt;do not&lt;/i&gt; + verb. We usually use the short form.</sectiontitle2>
<titlesound2>el_gram_3_2_4.mp3</titlesound2>
<text3>I do not drink coffee.</text3>
<text3a>&lt;b&gt;I don't drink&lt;/b&gt; coffee.</text3a>
<sound3>el_gram_3_2_5.mp3</sound3>
<text4>Most shops do not open on Sundays.</text4>
<text4a>Most shops &lt;b&gt;don't open&lt;/b&gt; on Sundays. </text4a>
<sound4>el_gram_3_2_6.mp3</sound4>
</section>
</grammar>